Therefore, both observations and numerical studies have pointed out how particle transport largely influences the efficiency of shock acceleration. Indeed, energetic particles can be scattered by the magnetic field fluctuations in resonance. The efficiency of such a scattering strongly depends on the fluctuation amplitude at the resonant scales. In case of very low (δB/B)2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
