A more realistic situation has been explored by Trotta et al. (2021) using a 2D hybrid code, where a turbulent jet generated by a 2.5D compressible MHD simulation can interact with an oblique supercritical shock wave. This aims at reproducing the shock dynamics when expanding in a highly turbulent medium. The level of turbulence is controlled by the values of δB/B0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
