Cosmic ray acceleration by large scale plasma motions with the ensemble of MHD shocks are expected to occur in a number of astrophysical objects including clusters of galaxies (Bykov et al. 2019b), clusters of massive stars with energetic stellar winds and supernovae shocks (Bykov et al. 2020), fast radiation-driven stellar winds (White and Chen 1994) and many others. The time dependent solutions of Eq. (43) for CR distribution started from a narrow range of particle momenta injected into the large scale compressible turbulence discussed in Bykov et al. (2019b) to model CRs in clusters of galaxies are approaching the asymptotic power law of the form F(p)∝p−5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
