				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$F(p) \propto p^{-5}$\end{document}. This is rather a soft CR spectrum which may explain the results of the recent analysis of the GeV regime gamma ray data from Fermi LAT on the Coma cluster (Adam et al. 2021). The direct measurements of the characteristics of the magnetic turbulence and cosmic rays are available in the heliosphere where detailed analysis of CR spectra in the quiet periods (i.e. in between of the events accompanied with shocks) revealed the spectra F(v)∝v−5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
